Peru Stocks: Alicorp, Ferreyros, La Cima, Relapasa, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-05-12T19:35:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/peru-stocks-alicorp-ferreyros-la-cima-relapasa-volcan.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 3:15 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index rose for the first session this
week, gaining 3.2 percent to 21,389.20. The MSCI All Peru Capped
Index rose 1.6 percent to 2,754.87.  Industrial stocks and utilities surged as an election poll
showed Congresswoman Keiko Fujimori rose to the lead ahead of
the June 5 presidential elections, said Estefany Castillo, an
analyst at Scotiabank Peru.  Alicorp SA (ALICORC1)  (ALICORC1 PE), Peru’s largest foodstuff maker,
advanced 5.7 percent to 5.92 soles. Refineria la Pampilla SA
(RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s Repsol YPF SA, rose 5.7 percent
to 1.85 soles. Corp. Aceros Arequipa SA (CORAREI1 PE), the Lima-
based steelmaker, climbed 4.8 percent to 2.85 soles.  Ferreyros
SA (FERREYC1)  (FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for Caterpillar
Inc., rose 3.8 percent to 3.27 soles.  Cementos Lima SA (CEMLIMI1)  (CEMLIMC1
PE), the country’s biggest cement maker, gained 3.7 percent to
2.80 soles.  Miners rose after metals rebounded in New York and  London .  Gold Fields La Cima SA (LACIMAI1 PE), a unit of Gold Fields
Ltd., jumped 7.1 percent to 4.50 soles.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO) 
, a Canadian gold exploration company, rose 6.1 percent
to $2.27.  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and
gold exploration company, gained 5.9 percent to 18 cents. Cia.
Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based silver and zinc
producer, rose 5.5 percent to 1.16 soles. Volcan Cia Minera SAA
(VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc producer, climbed 5 percent
to 3.36 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in  Lima  at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  